ther capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen was born in 1550, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Edwarde Milnes. She died in 1598, in her hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1550–1598":"1550–1598","1550–1583":"1550–1583","1570–1617":"1570–1617","1598":"1598","1550":"1550","1583":"1583","1570":"1570","1617":"1617","about 1570":"umbes 1570","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Flixton, Lancashire, England":"Flixton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1550–1598":"1550–1598","1550–1583":"1550–1583","1570–1617":"1570–1617","1598":"1598","1550":"1550","1583":"1583","1570":"1570","1617":"1617","about 1570":"noin 1570","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flixton, Lancashire, England":"Flixton, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1550–1598":"1550–1598","1550–1583":"1550–1583","1570–1617":"1570–1617","1598":"1598","1550":"1550","1583":"1583","1570":"1570","1617":"1617","about 1570":"environ 1570","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Flixton, Lancashire, England":"Flixton, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Ellen est née en 1550, à Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Edwarde Milnes. Elle est décédée en 15